CONTEXT CompositionISAsiblingAC IN ENGLISH

PURPOSE CONTEXT CompositionISAsiblingAC
{+ Test composition with sibling ISA types (A and B both subtypes of C).
   Given A ISA C and B ISA C, test r[W*A];s[C*Z] where join(A,C) = C exists.
   This should PASS because the type checker can find join C. +}

CLASSIFY A ISA C
CLASSIFY B ISA C

RELATION r[W*A]
RELATION s[C*Z]
RELATION result[W*Z]

RULE testCompositionISASibling: result = r;s

ENDCONTEXT
